=09
<meta name=3D"DC.Creator" content=3D"Weisstein, Eric W.">
=09
<meta name=3D"DC.Description" content=3D"The derivative of a function repre=
sents an infinitesimal change in the function with respect to one of its va=
riables. The &quot;simple&quot; derivative of a function f with respect to =
a variable x is denoted either f^'(x) or  (df)/(dx),  (1)   often written i=
n-line as df/dx. When derivatives are taken with respect to time, they are =
often denoted using Newton's overdot notation for fluxions,  (dx)/(dt)=3Dx^=
..  (2)   The &quot;d-ism&quot; of Leibniz's df/dt eventually won the notat=
ion battle...">
=09
